File: A general view of a corridor at Somerset Hospital in Cape Town, on July 02, 2020. (AFP) CAPE TOWN - Two patients have been killed and a police officer is seriously injured after being shot inside a Cape Town hospital. The officer had taken a suspect to the Somerset hospital for medical treatment when a man in the ward grabbed his firearm and shot the officer. He then shot two patients who were close by. Both died on the scene. Their identities have not been released yet.